While the petrol price has hit record highs, the state of some of our roads remains a complete nightmare for motorists. Our reporters are on the road in the country's biggest metros to give us more details on this. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - One reason for the poor state of Johannesburg's roads is the Johannesburg Road Agency's (JRA) shortage of funds, according to Gauteng Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo. READ: Easter traffic: 20 people killed on Gauteng roads He has also blamed COVID-19 and the lockdown for halting work to fix roads. While the petrol price has hit record highs, the state of some of our roads remains a complete nightmare for motorists. eNCA's @LindokuhlXulu1 takes a look at the potholes issue in Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/j3ZbwGR7C4 Mamabolo says the department met with the JRA, who presented their challenges. These include financial challenges. "They were asking us to support them," he says. "There are roads that fall into other municipalities, so we shouldn't be looking at one player. We are all responsible". Watch the video above for more from Gauteng Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo.